Implications
Unregulated polarization by PHY packets may exacerbate diseases (e.g., cancer via prolonged depolarization) or interfere with development. Therapeutic modulation (e.g., bioelectric drugs) could mimic natural states. Future studies should quantify polarization thresholds.
Conclusion
Natural polarization ensures adaptive signaling, while PHY-induced versions introduce dysregulation via coherence and non-thermal mechanisms, potentially shifting beneficial processes toward harm.
